      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Substantive due process is a principle in constitutional law that protects fundamental rights from government interference. It's not just about following the letter of the law, but also ensuring that the law itself respects our deepest rights, like freedom of speech, privacy, and equal treatment. Historically, this concept has been crucial in landmark cases that have expanded civil liberties and protected minority rights, making it a powerful tool for ensuring justice and fairness in our society.",
      "source": "target",
